  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nIf you delete the quoted message of a reply, at first, it keeps the user info, but still loses the color, which is not right.\r\n\r\nAfterwards, if you reload, it then loses all user info.\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/11926403/0a32cadb-c79a-460b-94c7-69a5cf3354e5)\r\n\r\nIn the image above, you can see both. The reloaded state is the message above. The \"just deleted\" state is the second one.\r\nIgnore the Resend message.\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Send a message in a chat\r\n2. Reply to that message\r\n3. See that the user color changed\r\n4. Reload the app\r\n5. See that the quoted user info disapeared\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe user info that was previously availbe in a quoted message should still be available after the original message was deleted.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nMissing user color, then missing info completely\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status desktop version: master `03d4fbcc48f1db4c49fc2c9a99ff6de242d620eb`\r\n- Operating System: Ubuntu 20\r\n\r\n",
